column5: I live in peterborough ont, I'm a family man. I joined this site to meet new friends, swap some tips and too possibly meet some new fishing buddy's. I enjoy fishing for all species of fish. I fish rainbows, salmon, walleye, musky and Panfish. and so on! My wife says that I have 366 calender days in my year because I always manage to find that extra day to fish!! Lol.   I also flyfish, and tye my own flies, not an expert by no means but I enjoy it.  I own my own boat so I fish big water, but still enjoy the shore fishing as well.!!  Thanks for taking the time in reading my post.   Dwayne.
Welcome aboard. All you'll need to do is get involved a little here and you'll surely have an abundance of dudes to fish with.  Looking forward to your reports.
Guess a guy from Peterborough can't be all bad... I was born in Peterborough Civic and lived on Ford St (till I was 9 months old.. then I scrammed!) !
Hi Dwayne  Welcome to the community!  I look forward to hearing about your adventures on and near the water.    Cheers!

Welcome Dwayne.  You won't meet a better bunch of people right here.  I've met some friends on here I'll have for the rest of my life.  It's a great place and I look forward to your reports!
